SIMPLE: ideate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ideate
<hw>I*de"ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>ideatum</ets>. See
<er>Idea</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>The actual existence
supposed to correspond with an idea; the correlate in real existence to
the idea as a thought or existence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ideate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ideate
<hw>I*de"ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
form in idea; to fancy.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>ideated</qex> man . . . as he stood in the intellect of
God.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To apprehend in thought so as to fix and hold in the
mind; to memorize.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ideation</ent>⟦br⟧
